#
# WHAT IS OPENTIMESTAMPS?
# OpenTimestamps is a standard for creating and verifying blockchain-based timestamps.
# It creates a timestamp proof that can be independently verified against the Bitcoin
# blockchain without relying on any trusted third party.
#
# HOW IT WORKS:
# 1. A SHA256 hash of the file is computed
# 2. The hash is committed to the Bitcoin blockchain via a Merkle tree
# 3. The proof file (.ots) contains the Merkle path from your hash to the blockchain
# 4. Anyone can verify the timestamp by checking the Bitcoin blockchain
#
# VERIFICATION INSTRUCTIONS:
#
# 1. Install OpenTimestamps client:
#    pip install opentimestamps-client
#    OR
#    npm install -g opentimestamps
#
# 2. Verify the timestamp:
#    ots verify conversation_ledger.yaml.ots
#
# Expected output:
#    Success! Bitcoin block [height] attests existence as of [timestamp]
#
# 3. Upgrade the timestamp (makes verification faster):
#    ots upgrade conversation_ledger.yaml.ots
#
# 4. Get detailed information:
#    ots info conversation_ledger.yaml.ots
#
# SECURITY PROPERTIES:
# - Proves document existed at or before the Bitcoin block timestamp
# - Impossible to backdate (would require rewriting Bitcoin blockchain)
# - Impossible to forge (cryptographic Merkle tree proof)
# - Trustless verification (anyone can verify using public Bitcoin blockchain)
# - Permanent proof (as long as Bitcoin blockchain exists)
#
# MATHEMATICAL GUARANTEES:
# The OpenTimestamps proof provides a mathematical guarantee that this file
# existed at the time of the Bitcoin block. To fake this, an attacker would need to:
# 1. Control >51% of Bitcoin mining power
# 2. Rewrite Bitcoin blockchain history
# 3. Recreate all subsequent blocks
# 
# This is computationally infeasible, making the timestamp effectively immutable.
